<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>back in v27, flycheck-error-list and flycheck-verify-setup used to appear in a small buffer on the bottom of the frame. They are now hijacking the sides of my frame which is annoying, since i cant event read the error.</p> <p>why is that?</p> <p>flycheck docs advises this, but it doesnt work:</p> <p><a href="https://www.flycheck.org/en/latest/user/error-list.html">https://www.flycheck.org/en/latest/user/error-list.html</a></p> <pre><code>(add-to-list &#39;display-buffer-alist `(,(rx bos &quot;*Flycheck errors*&quot; eos) (display-buffer-reuse-window display-buffer-in-side-window) (side . bottom) (reusable-frames . visible) (window-height . 0.33))) </code></pre> <p>&#x200B;</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/bananafingerz"> /u/bananafingerz </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w3sqv4/flycheck_buffers_splitting_up_vertically_since/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/w3sqv4/flycheck_buffers_splitting_up_vertically_since/">[comments]</a></span>